<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1956-03-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1956-03-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="522" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d522">
                        <head>522. Telegram 1603 from Geneva<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d522fn1">Source: Department of State, Central Files,
                                611.93/3–756. Confidential; Niact; Limit Distribution.</note></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName>Geneva</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1956-03-07">March 7, 1956, 3
                                    p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <pb facs="d522-1" n="1" type="facsimile" xml:id="d522-1"/>
                        <p>1603. From <persName corresp="#p_JUA_1">Johnson</persName>.</p>
                        <p>Would appreciate information soonest on when Department plans release
                            reply to CHICOM March 4 statement and confirmation of text.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_GFC_1"><hi rend="strong">Gowen</hi></persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p>Note: Mr. Waddell’s office (FE) notified 3/7/12:15 p.m. LWH</p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>